 
<p>
A sheriff in Oklahoma (and other officials) were secretly recorded
talking about their
<a href="https://apnews.com/article/mccurtain-oklahoma-racist-killing-journalists-recording-196ab0bf32fe8a5c0b48ef25c0af3c9f">wish to murder various inconvenient people</a>.
They are trying to distract attention from this by claiming that making
the recording was a crime.
<p>
Arguably it was lawful to make the recording, but even if it wasn't,
that is no reason to tolerate officials whose idea of upholding laws
is to discuss ideas for murder.

